sql:
SELECT property_name, actual_value
FROM compound_properties
WHERE uncertainty > 0.4;

external_knowledge:
- The cetane number is a measure of the combustion quality of diesel fuel;
- The device and method used can affect the accuracy of the cetane number measurement;
- The most recent calibration of a device ensures its measurements are reliable.

- 'ignition' method refers to a specific type of measurement method used to determine certain properties of compounds;
- 'top 3 most significant properties' means the properties with the highest actual values for each compound;
- 'keen interest' refers to users with more than 5 access logs in the system.

